div {
  all: initial;
}


This rule will remove any styles previously applied to the <div>, except for unicode-bidi and direction.

Browser Compatibility

The all property is widely supported in modern browsers. It has been available across browsers since January 2020


Use Cases

Resetting Styles: Quickly remove all styles from an element to start with a clean slate.
Scoped Styling: Apply the all property within a specific container to prevent inherited styles from affecting its children.
